<p>Cooling the CPU is the biggest CPU when it comes to these smaller cases because you don‚Äôt have room for large coolers or normal radiator space. But if there‚Äôs one thing the M1 does right, it is CPU cooling.</p>

<p>You can fit up to a Noctua U9S or C14S quite well. Liquid cooling is even more impressive, the M1 can fit up to a 240mm AIO, in addition to dual intake fans blowing air up into the case, you can run a 9900K overclocked to 4.9 GHz at 1.25 volts.</p>

<p>If you‚Äôre considering overclocking the Ryzen 3000 series CPUs (the 12 core and 16 core CPUs) prioritizing cooling for them is incredibly important, and surprisingly, this ITX case gets the job done with ease.</p>

<p>But that‚Äôs not all:</p>

<p>The M1 can accommodate another 240mm radiator on the side of the case, meaning if you want to liquid cool both your CPU and GPU with separate 120mm coolers, you can with this case.</p>

<p>Better still, this case has three expansion slots, so you can fit a thick, powerful GPU like the EVGA 2080 Ti XC Ultra.</p>

<p>All in all, the Ncase M1 is the best case hands down when it comes to pure performance. If you‚Äôre going to use your mITX case to house some beefy parts, this is the case for you.</p>

