<p>The graphics card can be up to 210mm in length - that may not seem like a lot, but it can accommodate the rtx 2070 mini or the zotac 1080 ti mini.</p>

<p>For storage you can fit up to two 2.5‚Äù drives. CPU cooling is the biggest compromise, as the cooler height maxes out at 45mm which doesn‚Äôt seem like a lot, but you can still accommodate noctua L9i or L9a (depending on which CPU you go with) and can comfortably cool an i5 or Ryzen 5 CPU, which is adequate for 95% of games.</p>

<p>With a case like this portability is incredibly important, which is why the Skyreach 4 Mini‚Äôs  lightweight yet strong material is awesome.</p>

<p>This case is too small to fit even an SFX power supply, which may throw some of you off - instead, it uses a special power supply called an HDPlex 400AC, but you don‚Äôt need a power brick for the PSU.</p>

<p>ALthough the price is pretty high for what you‚Äôre getting, its compact size is uncontested by any case on the market. No other case is just 5 liters, no other case can fit in a backpack, and considering this tiny thing can still house an RTX 2070, it‚Äôs clearly well designed.</p>

